        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> [16 Montague Street, London.]</placeName>
                    <date>March 26<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I write one line to thank you for your note.— Your exception almost proves the rule.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I hope that you will before long continue &amp; complete your researches on mimetic forms.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Dear Sir</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Meldola had provided CD with an example of sexual difference in the ocelli on the wings of a species of butterfly (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8821.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Raphael Meldola, 24 March 1873</ref> and n. 1).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8821.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Raphael Meldola, 24 March 1873</ref> and n. 3.</note>
        </div>        
            
